  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "3:9-18 Here again is shown that all mankind are under the guilt of sin, as a burden; and under the government and dominion of sin, as enslaved to it, to work wickedness. This is made plain by several passages of Scripture from the Old Testament, which describe the corrupt and depraved state of all men, till grace restrain or change them. Great as our advantages are, these texts describe multitudes who call themselves Christians. Their principles and conduct prove that there is no fear of God before their eyes. And where no fear of God is, no good is to be looked for.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Whose mouth - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 10:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The apostle has not quoted this literally, but has given the sense. David in the psalm is describing his bitter enemies.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Cursing - Reproachful and opprobrious language, such as Shimei used in relation to David; 2 Samuel 16:5, 2 Samuel 16:7-8.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Cursing - Reproachful and opprobrious language, such as Shimei used in relation to David; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 16:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 16:7-8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Bitterness - In the psalm, deceits. The word \"bitterness\" is used to denote severity, harshness, cruelty; reproachful and malicious words. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
